  • Constructor Details

    • JobPanel

      public JobPanel()
      the JobPanel constructor provides the creation of the JTable used as graphic job list. The job list management is assigned to the two functions: addRow() that add Chop type jobs; addRow2() that add Stitch type jobs.

  • Method Details

    • AddRow

      public static void AddRow​(java.lang.Object[] row, java.io.File[] file)
      Called by ChopPanel, is used to add Chop jobs to the list.
      Parameters:
      row - is the Object array containing all the rows data
      file - is the file array containing all the file that have to be added one by one

    • AddRow2

      public static void AddRow2​(java.lang.Object[] row, java.io.File[] file2)
      Called by StitchPanel, is used to add Stitch jobs to the list.
      Parameters:
      row - is the Object array containing all the rows data
      file2 - is the file array containing all the filw that have to be added all togheter
